WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:06.360 --> 00:00:08.450
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:08.450 --> 00:00:12.620
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates,
obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:12.620 --> 00:00:16.620
What he said in his final moments
drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:16.620 --> 00:00:18.500
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:20.250
Go ahead.

7
00:00:20.250 --> 00:00:21.250
Find it!

8
00:00:21.250 --> 00:00:24.460
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:24.460 --> 00:00:29.130
People set their sights on the Grand Line
in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:29.130 --> 00:00:31.970
The world has truly entered
the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:33.300 --> 00:00:34.220
However...

12
00:00:43.440 --> 00:00:44.400
Let me see!

13
00:00:44.400 --> 00:00:45.110
Watch it!

14
00:00:45.110 --> 00:00:45.690
– Cut it out!
– Cut it out!

15
00:00:45.690 --> 00:00:47.860
Get 'em outta the way already!

16
00:00:46.440 --> 00:00:47.860
Really?! They're stuck?!

17
00:00:51.070 --> 00:00:52.070
This is hell.

18
00:00:52.070 --> 00:00:52.570
Dammit!

19
00:00:52.570 --> 00:00:53.450
This is the worst!

20
00:00:53.450 --> 00:00:54.370
I can't take this...

21
00:00:54.370 --> 00:00:56.740
Freakin' pirates...

22
00:00:56.740 --> 00:01:03.960
Even in this era, the majority of people do not aspire
to be pirates and do not pursue the One Piece.

23
00:01:04.170 --> 00:01:06.630
Yes, just like these individuals…

24
00:01:13.720 --> 00:01:15.220
"Dear Nami,

25
00:01:15.220 --> 00:01:17.640
You're a special pirate.

26
00:01:17.640 --> 00:01:20.560
Today's world is dominated by barbarians

27
00:01:20.560 --> 00:01:23.730
who rely on their devil fruit
powers and brute strength.

28
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:28.030
But you outsmart them all
with your wits and ingenuity!

29
00:01:28.030 --> 00:01:31.070
Nami, you're my shining light!"

30
00:01:31.070 --> 00:01:32.910
Hey! We've got a delivery!

31
00:01:32.910 --> 00:01:36.950
"I hope you continue to have
wonderful adventures!"

32
00:01:36.950 --> 00:01:37.740
Delivery!

33
00:01:37.740 --> 00:01:39.870
C'mon! Would it kill you to knock?!

34
00:01:39.870 --> 00:01:44.000
Glasses, young lady! You'll get hurt
if you don't wear them for your deliveries!

35
00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:45.880
I can't go. I've got plans.

36
00:01:45.880 --> 00:01:46.840
What...?!

37
00:01:46.840 --> 00:01:49.960
I'm about to go on the adventure of a lifetime!

38
00:01:50.470 --> 00:01:51.050
Later!

39
00:01:51.050 --> 00:01:51.880
Listen here.

40
00:01:51.880 --> 00:01:54.090
People aren't meant to live on their own.

41
00:01:54.090 --> 00:01:58.600
The greengrocer boys send money to their folks,
and they even just received promotions!

42
00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:02.020
Stop comparing me to those inhuman freaks!

43
00:02:02.020 --> 00:02:04.900
What's to compare?!
They actually work hard and–

44
00:02:05.980 --> 00:02:09.570
I even heard they played
a big part in the Summit War!

45
00:02:12.030 --> 00:02:13.490
Resignation's lookin' good...

46
00:02:13.490 --> 00:02:14.910
Should we fall back for now?!

47
00:02:14.910 --> 00:02:16.820
Negative! Circle around the back!

48
00:02:16.820 --> 00:02:17.580
Yes, sir!

49
00:02:20.620 --> 00:02:21.830
Big Bro!

50
00:02:22.330 --> 00:02:24.580
How's that tactic working out for you?

51
00:02:27.460 --> 00:02:30.210
This is why you can't move up
the ladder as fast as me.

52
00:02:30.880 --> 00:02:33.260
You need to loosen up more!

53
00:02:43.940 --> 00:02:47.060
Who else but Dracule Mihawk, of course!

54
00:02:47.060 --> 00:02:49.940
I got close enough to see his
hawk eyes, so trust me!

55
00:02:49.940 --> 00:02:51.570
Nah, it's Flower Sword Vista.

56
00:02:51.570 --> 00:02:52.570
Wrong.

57
00:02:52.570 --> 00:02:55.070
The world's greatest swordsman
is Roronoa Zoro!

58
00:02:55.070 --> 00:02:56.200
Roronoa?

59
00:02:56.200 --> 00:02:58.570
Didn't he already keel over though?

60
00:02:58.570 --> 00:02:59.330
Didn't he?

61
00:02:59.330 --> 00:02:59.950
He's alive.

62
00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:00.580
He's dead.

63
00:03:00.580 --> 00:03:01.740
He's alive!

64
00:03:01.740 --> 00:03:03.000
He's dead!

65
00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:06.000
I saw it in the newspaper! It said that he died!

66
00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:08.000
Hey! If you wanna read it, buy it!

67
00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:08.750
Afro's here!

68
00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:10.250
Go away, Afro!

69
00:03:10.250 --> 00:03:11.630
Little punks...!

70
00:03:12.920 --> 00:03:15.510
Cyborg shipwright Franky!

71
00:03:15.510 --> 00:03:20.510
We take a deep dive into the facts
behind his disappearance two years ago!

72
00:03:20.510 --> 00:03:39.490
<b>Tracking down the vanished</b>
<b>genius cyborg shipwright!</b>
<b>Shipwright Monthly
The Franky Special</b>

73
00:03:20.510 --> 00:03:25.140
<b>Yagara Rental Shop Owner</b>

74
00:03:21.010 --> 00:03:23.020
<b>Franky?</b>

75
00:03:21.010 --> 00:03:22.010
Franky?

76
00:03:22.010 --> 00:03:23.020
<b>I don't know...</b>

77
00:03:22.010 --> 00:03:25.140
I don't know... Maybe you could try the shipyards?

78
00:03:23.140 --> 00:03:25.140
<b>Maybe you could try the shipyards?</b>

79
00:03:25.140 --> 00:03:27.400
<b>Vice President Paulie
Galley-La Company</b>
You should be asking Mr. Iceburg about that stuff!

80
00:03:25.270 --> 00:03:27.400
<b>You should be asking</b>

81
00:03:26.020 --> 00:03:27.400
<b>Mr. Iceburg about that stuff</b>

82
00:03:27.400 --> 00:03:28.980
<b>Alice
Iceburg's Personal Secretary</b>
Please make an appointment.

83
00:03:27.600 --> 00:03:28.980
<b>Please make an appointment</b>

84
00:03:30.110 --> 00:03:31.650
We had hit a dead end.

85
00:03:30.140 --> 00:03:37.020
<b>At a Dead End...</b>

86
00:03:31.650 --> 00:03:37.030
But we managed to snag a photo
of Franky's stunning figure!

87
00:03:32.940 --> 00:03:37.020
<b>The Stunning True Image of the Man...</b>

88
00:03:38.450 --> 00:03:39.490
What the h–

89
00:03:40.490 --> 00:03:41.990
No one buys this crap anyway...

90
00:03:41.990 --> 00:03:43.240
You said it.

91
00:03:49.790 --> 00:03:53.250
"By the way, Nami, I noticed
Captain Luffy's message too!

92
00:03:53.250 --> 00:03:57.340
'3D2Y'! They published it in the newspaper!

93
00:03:57.970 --> 00:04:02.100
I also knew it was a trick
to deceive the Marines!

94
00:04:02.720 --> 00:04:04.970
The key was how many times he rang the bell!

95
00:04:04.970 --> 00:04:09.020
The number was a clever reference to
Sabaody's sea cucumber spawn cycle!

96
00:04:09.020 --> 00:04:11.400
And today is the exact day they spawn!

97
00:04:11.400 --> 00:04:16.530
The Straw Hats will be reunited on
the Sabaody Archipelago today!

98
00:04:16.530 --> 00:04:22.160
That's how I knew to wait for you at the port
so that I could deliver this letter to you!"

99
00:04:28.920 --> 00:04:32.790
This street is never this crowded...

100
00:04:33.920 --> 00:04:35.920
Alright, time for plan B!

101
00:04:39.380 --> 00:04:39.880
Sorr–

102
00:04:40.380 --> 00:04:42.760
M-My skull's gonna crack...

103
00:04:42.760 --> 00:04:44.140
Must need more calcium.

104
00:04:44.140 --> 00:04:47.640
You should pound milk so that your
skull can take a pounding too!

105
00:04:47.640 --> 00:04:50.140
Was that a skull joke
just now?! It was, wasn't it?!

106
00:04:50.140 --> 00:04:52.020
What's with you guys?!

107
00:04:53.110 --> 00:04:54.520
I'm a lazy bum…

108
00:04:54.520 --> 00:04:56.230
My room's full of merch...

109
00:04:56.230 --> 00:04:57.860
I keep buying the same merch...

110
00:04:56.230 --> 00:04:58.110
Pipe down, will you?!

111
00:04:57.860 --> 00:05:01.820
I always listen to the same song...

112
00:04:58.110 --> 00:05:01.820
I wonder if he headed to the right ship...

113
00:05:01.820 --> 00:05:03.200
Zoro is alive.

114
00:05:03.200 --> 00:05:06.950
He's obviously out there getting stronger!

115
00:05:06.950 --> 00:05:08.330
Oni Hihi!

116
00:05:08.330 --> 00:05:09.330
What was that?

117
00:05:09.330 --> 00:05:10.210
Oni Giri.

118
00:05:10.210 --> 00:05:12.080
No, it wasn't!

119
00:05:10.960 --> 00:05:12.080
You making fun of him?

120
00:05:12.080 --> 00:05:13.580
Why does he chew on a sword?

121
00:05:13.580 --> 00:05:15.460
More is not always better!

122
00:05:15.460 --> 00:05:16.340
Mohh...

123
00:05:16.340 --> 00:05:16.960
What?

124
00:05:16.960 --> 00:05:17.590
Moss.

125
00:05:17.590 --> 00:05:18.590
Why though?!

126
00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:20.220
'Cause he has a moss head!

127
00:05:24.350 --> 00:05:26.470
What pissed him off?

128
00:05:26.890 --> 00:05:29.060
That's not just any card.

129
00:05:29.060 --> 00:05:32.230
That's an important key to
the future of Sabaody's security.

130
00:05:32.230 --> 00:05:33.980
Deliver it ASAP.

131
00:05:33.980 --> 00:05:35.610
Treat it with care.

132
00:05:35.610 --> 00:05:37.480
What if I accidentally drop it?

133
00:05:38.990 --> 00:05:40.360
I won't drop it!

134
00:05:41.860 --> 00:05:43.490
What a scary guy.

135
00:05:43.490 --> 00:05:45.700
What were you thinking, cracking a joke?!

136
00:05:45.700 --> 00:05:51.500
During the Summit War, he single-handedly held back
a giant chunk of ice that would've crushed our battleship.

137
00:05:51.500 --> 00:05:56.750
Such a stalwart spirit is none other than
the Benevolent King of the Waves!

138
00:05:58.630 --> 00:06:00.130
He's so cute!

139
00:06:00.550 --> 00:06:03.630
Yikes! His cuteness takes me
by surprise every time!

140
00:06:03.630 --> 00:06:07.350
But Chopper is a pirate, and I'm a Marine...

141
00:06:07.350 --> 00:06:09.020
We're from different worlds...!

142
00:06:09.350 --> 00:06:12.730
But I could never bring myself to capture you!

143
00:06:13.600 --> 00:06:14.230
Hello.

144
00:06:14.230 --> 00:06:18.320
What happened to the activation passkey
for the new anti-pirate weapon?

145
00:06:18.320 --> 00:06:20.530
Someone is on their way with it.

146
00:06:20.530 --> 00:06:25.320
This experiment will be a proof of concept for
the eradication of all pirates from Sabaody!

147
00:06:25.320 --> 00:06:27.070
I'm counting on you.

148
00:06:28.830 --> 00:06:30.950
Oh, Chopper...

149
00:06:30.950 --> 00:06:33.040
I wonder where you are at this moment...

150
00:06:33.920 --> 00:06:35.710
What is he supposed to be?

151
00:06:35.710 --> 00:06:37.880
"The Franky Special"?! Awesome!

152
00:06:37.880 --> 00:06:40.710
Huh... So that robot's famous or something?

153
00:06:38.290 --> 00:06:40.710
"The Anatomy of Franky"...

154
00:06:40.710 --> 00:06:42.210
Is he okay?!

155
00:06:42.210 --> 00:06:44.510
Scary!

156
00:06:47.220 --> 00:06:48.550
He didn't buy it either.

157
00:06:48.550 --> 00:06:50.930
You left the key in the back door!

158
00:06:51.560 --> 00:06:52.680
And the other day...

159
00:06:55.850 --> 00:06:58.480
I lost half an hour to depression!

160
00:06:58.480 --> 00:07:01.230
I don't even wanna think
about what happens if I'm late!

161
00:07:00.400 --> 00:07:01.230
Oops.

162
00:07:01.230 --> 00:07:01.980
I'm sor–

163
00:07:02.740 --> 00:07:04.360
The younger greengrocer!

164
00:07:07.160 --> 00:07:08.120
Phew!

165
00:07:08.120 --> 00:07:10.490
I can't be bothered with him...

166
00:07:11.120 --> 00:07:11.700
Wait...!

167
00:07:11.700 --> 00:07:14.620
Nope. Never dropped it.

168
00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:16.080
That's my–

169
00:07:18.540 --> 00:07:20.920
Ouch...!

170
00:07:20.920 --> 00:07:24.300
The ground sure is uneven around here.

171
00:07:24.300 --> 00:07:25.420
You just...!

172
00:07:34.060 --> 00:07:34.930
Move your stuff.

173
00:07:39.400 --> 00:07:43.480
A little fly like you should
stay hidden or get swatted.

174
00:07:54.830 --> 00:07:56.000
Hey, is this your...?

175
00:08:00.130 --> 00:08:02.630
Whoa, whoa! Wh-What's
wrong?! Are you hurt?!

176
00:08:02.630 --> 00:08:05.630
No, I'm just having a rough day...

177
00:08:05.630 --> 00:08:09.140
A Marine picked up my letter, and...

178
00:08:09.140 --> 00:08:12.010
Just a second ago, I passed
a Marine with a letter.

179
00:08:12.010 --> 00:08:12.760
Wh-What?!

180
00:08:12.760 --> 00:08:14.680
He went in there.

181
00:08:19.480 --> 00:08:22.570
Alright, let me teach you
a special magic phrase.

182
00:08:22.570 --> 00:08:24.030
Ready?

183
00:08:24.030 --> 00:08:26.780
"I'm waiting for someone,
so just water for now!"

184
00:08:26.780 --> 00:08:28.490
...so just water for now!

185
00:08:28.490 --> 00:08:30.360
Take a hike, kid!

186
00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:32.490
Numb nuts, the best was Whitebeard!

187
00:08:32.490 --> 00:08:34.990
He wasn't a swordsman, though!
He used a naginata!

188
00:08:34.990 --> 00:08:37.120
It's Mihawk! I saw it myself!

189
00:08:37.120 --> 00:08:38.870
You saw his "hawk eyes." Sure. Right.

190
00:08:38.870 --> 00:08:41.250
With these very eyes!

191
00:08:41.630 --> 00:08:43.250
You're all kidding yourselves!

192
00:08:43.250 --> 00:08:44.840
The greatest is...

193
00:08:44.840 --> 00:08:45.880
Akainu, of course.

194
00:08:45.880 --> 00:08:47.880
– This is about the greatest swordsman!
– This is about the greatest swordsman!

195
00:08:47.880 --> 00:08:50.130
It's obviously Blackbeard since
he took out Whitebeard!

196
00:08:47.880 --> 00:08:49.930
These guys have no eyes for talent…

197
00:08:49.930 --> 00:08:53.260
Taking future potential into account,
it's clearly Zoro, right?

198
00:08:50.130 --> 00:08:52.720
It's always -beard this and -beard
that with you, isn't it?!

199
00:08:52.720 --> 00:08:55.180
An Emperor is obviously better
than a Warlord! It's Red Hair!

200
00:08:53.260 --> 00:08:56.270
Who talks about Moss Head
without considering Black Leg?

201
00:08:55.180 --> 00:08:56.270
Wait, so Buggy the Clown...?!

202
00:08:59.390 --> 00:09:00.140
Him?! No way!

203
00:09:00.140 --> 00:09:01.770
His bounty is lower than Zoro's!

204
00:09:01.770 --> 00:09:04.520
There's no way this is the world's greatest!

205
00:09:08.400 --> 00:09:11.030
What pissed him off?

206
00:09:11.780 --> 00:09:14.120
Relax, guys, or we'll be here all day.

207
00:09:14.120 --> 00:09:16.490
Let's narrow it down to the young pirates.

208
00:09:15.120 --> 00:09:16.490
Success!

209
00:09:16.490 --> 00:09:17.790
Oh, the Worst Generation?

210
00:09:18.160 --> 00:09:20.290
Trafalgar, Captain Kid...

211
00:09:20.290 --> 00:09:20.790
Zoro!

212
00:09:20.790 --> 00:09:22.170
And Straw Hat. Oh, it's that one!

213
00:09:22.170 --> 00:09:23.670
I knew you'd be hiding here!

214
00:09:26.800 --> 00:09:28.420
Big Bro!

215
00:09:28.420 --> 00:09:29.800
Why aren't you at work?

216
00:09:29.800 --> 00:09:32.760
Because I've been handed
the fate of that new weapon.

217
00:09:32.760 --> 00:09:35.180
Put it away! That's classified!

218
00:09:35.180 --> 00:09:35.930
So...

219
00:09:35.930 --> 00:09:38.470
who do you think is the greatest?

220
00:09:38.470 --> 00:09:41.850
I know his favorite! It's Straw Hat Luffy!

221
00:09:41.850 --> 00:09:42.980
– Oh?!
– Oh?!

222
00:09:42.980 --> 00:09:44.480
Lay it on us!
Straw Hat?!

223
00:09:44.480 --> 00:09:47.730
What, are you guys rooting for pirates?

224
00:09:48.360 --> 00:09:50.110
– No, no!
– That's not what this is about!

225
00:09:50.110 --> 00:09:53.070
Hey now... He's a bit of wet blanket, is all...

226
00:09:53.070 --> 00:09:55.870
This is why you can't move up
the ladder as fast as me.

227
00:09:55.870 --> 00:09:58.660
What's this? Does your
little brother outrank you?

228
00:09:58.660 --> 00:10:02.000
He always says one word
too many! He's such a jerk!

229
00:09:59.450 --> 00:10:01.370
As a younger brother, you know…

230
00:10:01.370 --> 00:10:04.960
I didn't see him much,
but I ended up outranking him!

231
00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:05.500
And as usual, the big brother
lets him say whatever he wants.

232
00:10:04.960 --> 00:10:07.170
Were you guys in the Summit War?

233
00:10:05.500 --> 00:10:09.380
Can you still love your little brother
when he's such a jerk?

234
00:10:07.170 --> 00:10:10.760
We were! Big Bro got stuck on some ice!

235
00:10:10.760 --> 00:10:13.760
I can't stand my brother.

236
00:10:10.760 --> 00:10:12.510
That's quite something, huh?

237
00:10:12.510 --> 00:10:13.760
Yeah, how do I put this…?

238
00:10:13.760 --> 00:10:15.590
He needs to loosen up!

239
00:10:15.590 --> 00:10:18.220
Loosen up!

240
00:10:18.220 --> 00:10:20.810
You need to loosen up more!

241
00:10:24.060 --> 00:10:24.980
I...

242
00:10:26.150 --> 00:10:28.110
can't stand my brother.

243
00:10:39.580 --> 00:10:41.950
Wh-What happened?!

244
00:11:15.070 --> 00:11:17.320
Big Bro!

245
00:11:17.910 --> 00:11:20.830
Where are you, Big Bro?!

246
00:11:29.750 --> 00:11:32.710
Big Bro!

247
00:11:41.350 --> 00:11:44.230
I'm your brother!

248
00:11:45.560 --> 00:11:47.560
That sling slips off easily, doesn't it?

249
00:11:48.100 --> 00:11:50.940
The general issue ones suck!

250
00:11:50.940 --> 00:11:52.110
I'm good.

251
00:11:52.110 --> 00:11:53.980
Your shoulders are sloped, too.

252
00:11:54.940 --> 00:11:57.320
You need to loosen up more!

253
00:11:59.740 --> 00:12:00.870
Big Bro...!

254
00:12:02.240 --> 00:12:05.620
Run for it!

255
00:12:15.760 --> 00:12:20.050
If Gold Roger hadn't triggered
the start of the Great Pirate Era...

256
00:12:22.050 --> 00:12:24.060
If Fire Fist Ace hadn't been caught...

257
00:12:26.020 --> 00:12:29.060
If we hadn't been called up to this war...

258
00:12:32.820 --> 00:12:35.570
If I hadn't been trapped under that giant's leg...

259
00:12:37.650 --> 00:12:40.070
If the sling hadn't broken...

260
00:12:41.240 --> 00:12:43.830
If I hadn't heard that man's voice...

261
00:12:45.700 --> 00:12:50.460
Every little thing is changing my life bit by bit.

262
00:12:52.380 --> 00:12:54.840
If I can survive and get back home...

263
00:12:54.840 --> 00:12:59.590
could I also become the catalyst
for changing someone's life someday?

264
00:13:05.720 --> 00:13:07.600
Just like that guy.

265
00:13:11.730 --> 00:13:14.980
My brother is here thanks to Straw Hat.

266
00:13:14.980 --> 00:13:19.490
But he lost his brother Ace
right before his eyes.

267
00:13:19.900 --> 00:13:22.030
He's been missing ever since.

268
00:13:22.780 --> 00:13:25.200
I wonder how he's doing now.

269
00:13:25.830 --> 00:13:29.080
This is urgent! The Straw Hat
Pirates have been sighted!

270
00:13:29.080 --> 00:13:30.540
– Straw Hat?!
– Straw Hat?!

271
00:13:30.540 --> 00:13:34.170
It seems they will address their
new crew members at Grove 46!

272
00:13:35.170 --> 00:13:36.550
So that means...

273
00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:38.300
I can meet Nami!

274
00:13:39.800 --> 00:13:43.470
Where's Nami?!

275
00:13:44.090 --> 00:13:47.850
A bunch of Marines just rushed in
and started fighting pirates!

276
00:13:48.470 --> 00:13:50.680
And you couldn't be more obviously fake!

277
00:13:50.680 --> 00:13:53.730
I mean, really?! You call that
pulling off Nami?!

278
00:13:53.730 --> 00:13:55.860
Do your research!

279
00:13:55.860 --> 00:13:57.860
If I were her, I would've...

280
00:13:57.860 --> 00:14:00.240
What? What? No, no...

281
00:14:00.240 --> 00:14:01.860
Oh, crap!

282
00:14:01.860 --> 00:14:04.370
Son of a bitch!

283
00:14:04.370 --> 00:14:07.030
Soul King's final show
on the tour was sold out…

284
00:14:07.030 --> 00:14:08.240
– Alright!
– Yeah!

285
00:14:08.240 --> 00:14:09.160
Reading is free!

286
00:14:09.160 --> 00:14:12.160
Yeah, let's take a look!

287
00:14:16.460 --> 00:14:17.630
She's crying...

288
00:14:18.130 --> 00:14:20.130
You damn barbarians!

289
00:14:21.840 --> 00:14:24.470
The pacifista are here!

290
00:14:29.890 --> 00:14:31.390
Gum-Gum...

291
00:14:33.640 --> 00:14:35.400
Jet...

292
00:14:36.900 --> 00:14:39.440
Pistol!

293
00:14:41.360 --> 00:14:42.110
What the hell...

294
00:14:42.690 --> 00:14:44.110
Looks like he's doing fine.

295
00:14:48.370 --> 00:14:52.620
Straw Hat Luffy downed a pacifista
with a single blow?!

296
00:14:52.620 --> 00:14:53.870
Incredible...!

297
00:14:53.870 --> 00:14:55.870
Lieutenant Commander, activate it!

298
00:14:55.870 --> 00:15:01.590
But that weapon releases a toxic fluid into the sea
that dissolves ships right through their coatings.

299
00:15:01.590 --> 00:15:03.470
It could affect the ecosystem...

300
00:15:03.470 --> 00:15:04.840
Shut the hell up!

301
00:15:04.840 --> 00:15:07.510
Do whatever it takes to drown Straw Hat!

302
00:15:09.350 --> 00:15:12.770
Of all the ships, it had to be
the one Chopper is on...

303
00:15:12.770 --> 00:15:14.520
But I...!

304
00:15:14.520 --> 00:15:17.270
I...!

305
00:15:17.270 --> 00:15:20.070
– You can still see Soul King!
– You can still see Soul King!

306
00:15:20.070 --> 00:15:21.610
Soul King is Brook!

307
00:15:21.610 --> 00:15:23.190
They say he went to Grove 42!

308
00:15:23.190 --> 00:15:24.360
He's a Straw Hat Pirate!

309
00:15:24.360 --> 00:15:26.320
He flew straight from the venue!

310
00:15:26.320 --> 00:15:28.870
– We'll take you!
– We'll take you!

311
00:15:29.450 --> 00:15:30.830
No thank you!

312
00:15:30.830 --> 00:15:31.830
Don't be shy!

313
00:15:31.830 --> 00:15:33.620
We'll take you...

314
00:15:33.620 --> 00:15:34.620
as a hosta–

315
00:15:38.210 --> 00:15:39.960
Ugh! It's the older greengrocer!

316
00:15:39.960 --> 00:15:42.340
Wait...! Aren't you the wholesaler's kid?!

317
00:15:41.590 --> 00:15:42.960
No, I'm not!

318
00:15:42.960 --> 00:15:44.510
What are you doing here?!

319
00:15:44.510 --> 00:15:45.590
It's dangerous!

320
00:15:45.590 --> 00:15:46.340
Hey!

321
00:15:46.340 --> 00:15:46.880
Huh?

322
00:15:46.880 --> 00:15:48.010
This is as far as we go.

323
00:15:48.010 --> 00:15:49.890
Dark King Rayleigh is in our way!

324
00:15:49.220 --> 00:15:49.890
Rayleigh?!

325
00:15:50.510 --> 00:15:52.260
So he's still alive?

326
00:15:52.260 --> 00:15:53.350
Let's go around.

327
00:15:53.350 --> 00:15:56.140
It'll take 30 minutes to get to Grove 42.

328
00:15:57.640 --> 00:15:58.900
Let's make a deal.

329
00:15:58.900 --> 00:16:01.060
I can get us there in ten.

330
00:16:01.440 --> 00:16:04.820
You wanna catch Straw Hat, right?

331
00:16:04.820 --> 00:16:06.950
I said, "Let's make a deal"!

332
00:16:06.950 --> 00:16:09.070
Why would I agree to putting you in danger?!

333
00:16:09.070 --> 00:16:10.700
Let's get you home to your mom.

334
00:16:10.700 --> 00:16:12.330
Don't treat me like a kid!

335
00:16:12.330 --> 00:16:14.540
I'm already fifteen, you know?!

336
00:16:14.540 --> 00:16:18.000
I told you! We're not pirates!

337
00:16:19.460 --> 00:16:23.090
What? Why did they run away...?

338
00:16:25.840 --> 00:16:29.220
– My Franky!
– My Zoro!

339
00:16:30.340 --> 00:16:33.600
We really made it past the square already...

340
00:16:33.600 --> 00:16:35.600
I know, right? So it's a deal!

341
00:16:35.600 --> 00:16:36.600
No, it's not!

342
00:16:36.600 --> 00:16:38.600
Why not?!

343
00:16:37.230 --> 00:16:38.600
Let's get you ho–

344
00:16:47.570 --> 00:16:48.700
What's with the big bugs?!

345
00:16:48.700 --> 00:16:49.820
Why are they after us?

346
00:16:49.820 --> 00:16:52.320
It's looking right at you! What did you do?!

347
00:16:52.320 --> 00:16:55.700
Ugh, stop causing trouble!
I need to go to see Nami!

348
00:16:55.700 --> 00:16:56.830
Not a chance.

349
00:16:56.830 --> 00:17:00.080
It's my duty to protect civilians
like you from dangerous pira–

350
00:17:00.080 --> 00:17:02.080
Nami's not a dangerous pirate!

351
00:17:02.080 --> 00:17:03.840
But she is a pirate.

352
00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:05.840
Yeah. She's a pirate.

353
00:17:05.840 --> 00:17:06.840
But it's different...

354
00:17:07.590 --> 00:17:10.510
She changed my life!

355
00:17:11.220 --> 00:17:15.350
I didn't eat a devil fruit,
and I don't have muscles like you!

356
00:17:15.850 --> 00:17:19.980
In this era where strength means everything...

357
00:17:21.980 --> 00:17:25.480
I thought a weak girl like me
could never live freely!

358
00:17:27.480 --> 00:17:33.490
Nami is my everything. She showed me
that even I can go on adventures too.

359
00:17:33.870 --> 00:17:35.660
That's why I'm gonna cheer her on!

360
00:17:35.660 --> 00:17:36.580
But you...

361
00:17:39.660 --> 00:17:41.460
I can't let you meet her directly,

362
00:17:41.460 --> 00:17:43.830
but I'll allow you to see her from a distance.

363
00:17:43.830 --> 00:17:44.750
What?!

364
00:17:44.750 --> 00:17:47.130
I'll inform the Marines about the shortcut.

365
00:17:47.550 --> 00:17:50.260
We'll do our best to arrest Straw Hat.

366
00:17:50.880 --> 00:17:53.930
What's the point of telling me all that now?

367
00:17:56.390 --> 00:17:58.770
Someone left the key in the...

368
00:17:58.770 --> 00:18:00.180
Is this a back door?!

369
00:18:01.310 --> 00:18:04.440
♪ Sit right back, I’ll tell you ‘bout a hero! ♪

370
00:18:04.980 --> 00:18:06.820
I'm rushing there, too!

371
00:18:04.980 --> 00:18:08.690
– ♪ He'll be king someday, there's no need to fear-o! ♪
– ♪ He'll be king someday, there's no need to fear-o! ♪

372
00:18:07.190 --> 00:18:08.690
I just got held up a bit...

373
00:18:08.690 --> 00:18:11.820
Hey!

374
00:18:11.820 --> 00:18:13.320
There's a giant bird!

375
00:18:13.320 --> 00:18:16.030
Monkey D. Luffy is confirmed
to be on its back!

376
00:18:16.030 --> 00:18:19.200
The Straw Hats are going to reunite!

377
00:18:19.200 --> 00:18:21.790
Thanks! I think I can make it in time!

378
00:18:21.790 --> 00:18:23.460
You can't see her in person!

379
00:18:25.380 --> 00:18:28.340
Y'know, I think you've changed a little.

380
00:18:28.920 --> 00:18:31.380
Did something happen during the war?

381
00:18:31.380 --> 00:18:33.720
I guess you could say that.

382
00:18:34.090 --> 00:18:35.220
Thanks to him–

383
00:18:39.350 --> 00:18:41.980
Thanks for carrying me this far!

384
00:18:41.980 --> 00:18:44.480
I move up the ladder so slowly...

385
00:18:57.070 --> 00:19:00.540
Boss, it seems I've caught a little fly.

386
00:19:00.540 --> 00:19:01.700
That works out!

387
00:19:01.700 --> 00:19:03.410
Stay there and keep an eye on her.

388
00:19:03.410 --> 00:19:06.040
That job perfectly suits a spoiled rich kid.

389
00:19:07.960 --> 00:19:09.710
Let's get one thing clear...

390
00:19:09.710 --> 00:19:14.050
What suits me is to sink the Straw Hat's ship
with the new weapon and make a name for myself.

391
00:19:14.050 --> 00:19:15.090
Sink?

392
00:19:15.090 --> 00:19:17.090
No! You can't do that!

393
00:19:20.930 --> 00:19:21.850
Nami...!

394
00:19:21.850 --> 00:19:22.640
She'll die–

395
00:19:34.070 --> 00:19:37.700
A little fly like you shouldn't
be buzzing around my ears.

396
00:19:50.670 --> 00:19:53.210
I won't be able to see her in person...

397
00:19:53.760 --> 00:19:57.090
I can only watch as their ship is sunk…

398
00:19:58.090 --> 00:20:02.600
I can't even hand her a single letter...

399
00:20:19.240 --> 00:20:21.160
Civilians are attacking us!

400
00:20:20.240 --> 00:20:21.910
I'm gonna see Soul King!

401
00:20:21.910 --> 00:20:23.370
Let go of me!

402
00:20:22.870 --> 00:20:23.370
Huh?

403
00:20:31.590 --> 00:20:33.550
Th-The passkey!

404
00:20:33.550 --> 00:20:35.510
C-Catch her!

405
00:20:35.510 --> 00:20:36.880
Retrieve it quickly!

406
00:20:36.880 --> 00:20:39.130
We won't be able to activate it in time!

407
00:20:39.130 --> 00:20:41.890
What's wrong with you idiots?!
She's just a kid!

408
00:20:48.020 --> 00:20:50.480
I-It's the Benevolent King of the Waves!

409
00:20:55.400 --> 00:20:59.030
"Nami, you're my shining light!

410
00:21:00.450 --> 00:21:05.290
In this world where strength means everything,
even if I get hurt and trampled on,

411
00:21:05.290 --> 00:21:10.210
I still want to fight, run,
and live as freely as I can.

412
00:21:10.210 --> 00:21:14.040
I believe that now thanks to you.

413
00:21:16.550 --> 00:21:17.710
I hope...

414
00:21:17.710 --> 00:21:20.300
you continue to have...

415
00:21:20.300 --> 00:21:22.050
wonderful adventures!"

416
00:21:31.270 --> 00:21:35.900
Set sail!

417
00:21:53.960 --> 00:21:58.590
S-Straw Hat's ship is out of firing range...

418
00:22:01.090 --> 00:22:03.510
You little...! What the hell are you doing?!

419
00:22:03.510 --> 00:22:05.800
Hey now... Kids are impulsive.

420
00:22:05.800 --> 00:22:07.220
What do you mean, "impulsive"?!

421
00:22:07.220 --> 00:22:09.430
She destroyed classified material.

422
00:22:07.720 --> 00:22:09.180
Damn it...!

423
00:22:09.180 --> 00:22:10.980
They got away…!

424
00:22:09.430 --> 00:22:10.980
That's a criminal act!

425
00:22:11.350 --> 00:22:12.850
It could even be a felony...

426
